President Trump held a roundtable discussion at the White House with women entrepreneurs and small business leaders. The President emphasized the importance of empowering and promoting women in business and acknowledged the significant role they play as job creators and leaders. He also highlighted the economic benefits of having women in senior leadership roles and expressed his commitment to addressing the barriers faced by women professionals and entrepreneurs. Ivanka Trump, Vice President Mike Pence, and Small Business Administration Administrator Linda McMahon also participated in the discussion and shared their support for women in business. Several women entrepreneurs shared their personal stories and the impact they are making in their communities. The President and his administration pledged to continue advocating for policies that support working families, including affordable childcare and access to capital and markets.